article.description: Curry, Kent lead hot-shooting JMU past Hofstra, 82-73
article.headline: Curry, Kent lead hot-shooting JMU past Hofstra, 82-73
article.linkText: Curry, Kent lead hot-shooting JMU past Hofstra, 82-73
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Ron Curry had 20 points and a career-high 11 assists, Jackson Kent scored a career-best 20 on 7-of-10 shooting, and James Madison shot a season-high 63 percent from the field to beat Hofstra 83-72 Saturday. Curry hit a career-high tying five 3-pointers on six attempts. Yohanny Dalembert added 14 points for James Madison (19-12, 12-6 Colonial Athletic Association), which never trailed and made 27 of 43 field goals, including 10 of 17 (59 percent) from 3-point range. The Dukes used an 18-3 run to close the first half and led 41-25 at the break. Hofstra used a 20-4 run to pull within three on Ameen Tanksley's 3-pointer with 13:44 to play. Back-to-back 3's by Jackson and Curry made it 66-55 with 9:03 remaining and the Pride (19-12, 10-8) trailed by at least nine the rest of the way. Brian Bernardi led Hofstra with 22 points and Dion Nesmith added 14.
